A custom 9-key macropad with a rotary encoder, built using a custom PCB and powered by QMK firmware. The macropad supports multiple modes (Study, Creative, Focus) to provide different shortcut mappings based on workflow.

Hardware Supported
- Custom 3x3 macropad PCB  
- Seeed XIAO RP2040  
- 9 MX-style mechanical switches  
- EC11 rotary encoder  

Build
Make example for this keyboard (after setting up your QMK environment):
qmk compile -kb shubhmacropad -km default

Flash
Flashing example for this keyboard:
qmk flash -kb shubhmacropad -km default

Or manually:
- Double press reset on the XIAO RP2040  
- Drag and drop the .uf2 file onto the device  

Bootloader
Enter the bootloader in the following ways:
- Double press the reset button on the XIAO RP2040  
- Plug in the board while pressing reset  
- Use the reset pads/button on the PCB if available  
